Australian Grand Prix: F1 drivers raring to go in Australia
Drivers including Sebastian Vettel, Daniel Ricciardo, Jenson Button and Max Verstappen look forward to theseason-opening Australian Grand Prix.Toro Rosso rookie Verstappen says he will treat the event as "just another weekend" as the 17-year old is set to becomes the youngest driver in history to take part in a Grand Prix.Other drivers giving their thoughts on the weekend ahead include Kimi Raikkonen, Kevin Magnussen, Valtteri Bottas and Romain Grosjean.Australian Grand Prix coverage details.Available to UK users only.